<br>
Here's an interesting thought.  If they opened a new server, gave us all the frills of Legends, but promised to enforce RP there, would any of you pay extra to play there?<br>
<br>
And please, no dull comments on how hard it would be to police RP, we all know that so there's no need to point it out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderating inconsistently<br>since Jun 2002</span><br>  Posts: 1321<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/02 5:51:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1454.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Verant's take on RPing on this server</span><hr size=1> Nope.<br>
<br>
For starters, forced RP sucks, because then you're stuck letting Verant decide what is and what isn't roleplay.<br>
<br>
For seconds, 40 bucks a month is a lot.<br>
<br>
For thirds, I think the way they've handled Legends shows that they'd fail to provide service.  They promised those Legends players dynamic content &amp; tons of GM quests and such, and I'm pretty sure they don't get it.  All they get is the cheesy webspace and some kind of GM enforced raid calendar garbage.<br>
<br>
There are some things I'd pay extra for, if it was guaranteed that I'd get them, enforced RP just isn't one of them:<br>
1) Ability to play as other race/class/diety combinations.<br>
2) Ability to play as a monster (project M)<br>
3) A permanent &quot;quest GM&quot; who just ran quests all day... some silly, some more serious (a $3.00 per month price increase would be sufficient to pay for one of these 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, and still give Verant a little extra on the side).  Especially if the quests were designed to help introduce players to more of the backstory of Norrath.<br>
4) Optional Zones (I'd be willing to pay a one time per zone fee to download special optional zones, like Broken Skull Rock or the Vasty Deep).<br>
<br>
The 40 dollar price tag on Legends is way too high, and too much of the benefits are felt outside of the game (world mapper, character webspace, etc).  I'd much rather pick and choose from a variety of special options that have a much lower price tag (some recurring monthly, others on a 1 time basis).<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroninsenshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoninSenshi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia</span><br>  Posts: 1081<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/02 5:56:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1454.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Verant's take on RPing on this server</span><hr size=1> It means they folded and given up on Roleplaying in their game. <p><IMG SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Shintou.gif" WIDTH="127" HEIGHT="110"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utukka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tukka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/02 5:57:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1454.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.atlantic.net/~tukka/glowhand.jpg height=44 width=44></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Verant's take on RPing on this server</span><hr size=1> Back before we had an RP server and everyone was telling me such a thing would never exist, my argument for the way a RP server &quot;should be&quot; involved enforced RP.  If someone said anything blatently OOC/OOG on a public channel (/say, /shout) you could be /reported and have your character on that server suspended or banned.<br>
<br>
I don't think I'd pay more for that though.  I can play any Simutronics game and get &quot;enforced&quot; RP and a better RP atmosphere all around.  EQ just isn't designed around RP and will never be a great platform for it, no matter what they do to change things now.  I'm not going to spend more money just for the RP environment to improve a little.<br>
<br>
Edit: To clarify, when I say &quot;enforced RP&quot;, I mean an enforced policy against blatently out of genre references.  I think that such a policy is used to relatively good effect in GS3, it's not the fascist state that you might imagine.  It's not perfect for preserving the integrity of the roleplaying atmosphere in the game either, but it does a better job than no enforcement whatsoever I think. <p><B><FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS">--Tukka</FONT></B><BR>
Player of <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=189682">Velsor Secarne</A> (on Firiona Vie)
<BR>
Shadow Knight of Cazic-Thule<BR>
Seeker of the Dark Truth
<BR>Officer of the <A HREF="http://www.indigovoid.net">Indigo Void</A></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utukka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tukka</A> at: 9/25/02 6:00:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubaldisking.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baldisking</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/02 6:26:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1454.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Verant's take on RPing on this server</span><hr size=1> Problem with enforced roleplay .. not enough people would remain on the server to leave it viable.  Enforce roleplay and you kill FV server.<br>
Lets face it, before the patches the population was pitiful. Still is in many places.<br>
<br>
I really think that people have to be a little more tolerant of others on this server.  And hey, that includes me!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uelhanamistfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ElhanaMistfall</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.mistfits.com/tgrobb/elhanaportsmall.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/02 6:31:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1454.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Verant's take on RPing on this server</span><hr size=1> Seriously speaking, RP is optional (and occasionally mocked) on all other servers.  While there are many different kinds of role-playing characters, at least it's more acceptable here on FV. <br>
<br>
I have mixed feelings about the recent patches. I believe removing alignment was a bad idea, but I think the alignment system should have been more dynamic... Instead of &quot;picking&quot; an alignment, I think alignment should have been handled a little more like faction (e.g. the more &quot;good&quot; faction you get, the more &quot;good&quot; your alignment would be&quot;). <br>
<br>
The reason for this is that I feel that the &quot;role&quot; being played by a person should be up to that person. If I want to play a dark elf, and Verant tells me I have to be a meanie and strive to kill High Elves, does that mean I'm *not* role playing if I want to be a nice/repentant dark elf?  Likewise, what's wrong with playing a powerhungry high elf wizard who forsakes his own kind for the darker secrets of the world?  Nothing. In both cases, you can roleplay who you want to be.   <br>
<br>
For me, role playing is playing the character you enjoy being, not what someone else thinks you should be. <p><center>
