<br>
Anyways, I'd love if they reinstated the old rules, except possibly with the grouping rules because I imagine that one would piss people off the most if they put it back in.<br>
<br>
I really miss the /alignment tho, it was my motivation to reach 10 for most of my characters.  Most of my characters post May 8th didn't see that far. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uelhanamistfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ElhanaMistfall</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.mistfits.com/tgrobb/elhanaportsmall.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/02 8:16:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1454.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Verant's take on RPing on this server</span><hr size=1> (( thanks for the welcome.. just as an aside, I have more than 1 post on our guild message board... this is just the first time I've felt inclined to post here))<br>
<br>
I personally would love to see alignment brought back in, but I don't know if that kind of retroactive change can be made (especially for characters made post-May 8th). <br>
<br>
I think it would have been interesting if, at level 10, you could &quot;shift&quot; your alignment one way (e.g. orderly to neutral, neutral to discordant, or vice-versa, or from good to neutral or neutral to evil, etc.) .. and then at level 20, had the same option... That way, someone who invested the time to take a character to level 20 would have the option of pretty much any alignment that suited their character.   <br>
<br>
I suppose, though, that the &quot;alignment&quot; option was largely in place to restrict grouping, and I wouldn't like to see that changed.  Of course, it was also used to restrict how your spells would affect others.  I remember one time in High Keep having to tell an injured dark elf that I could do nothing for her... <br>
<br>
Suffice to say, that I doubt any changes will be made to the server as it is now.  I sincerely hope that the /OOC channel is never brought in, and I wish that something was done more to restrict people using /auction or /shout as a form of OOC.  But... we can't have it all, can we?<br>
