</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthetranquil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Tranquil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Keeper of Lore and Elven Wine</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/02 8:37:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1454.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   FV</span><hr size=1> With the bazaar in place, I don't see why they don't restore /auc to city zones only.  It might even push people to purchase Luclin just so they can sell their wares; wow, VI would really like that I bet!  /shout's range limit was perfect.  You can /shout a train when and where it mattered, and people across the zone wouldn't have to hear it since it didn't pertain to them.  By leaving it as zone-wide, all they did was NOT encourage RP... I mean come on, if my character actually shouted for a group, I don't think that barbarian shaman 2 mountain ranges away would be able to hear him.  And, as far as alignment goes, why not just include BONUSES?  If a group is all together of similar alignments, they get an XP bonus... that way if two characters really had to group and were of different alignments, they can, but won't suffer a penalty for it.<br>
<br>
The population may have been small before May 8th, but at least it felt more like a roleplaying game and less like Diablo.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uelhanamistfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ElhanaMistfall</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.mistfits.com/tgrobb/elhanaportsmall.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/02 8:46:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1454.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FV</span><hr size=1> That's a good idea, Tranquil..perhaps that's something that should be suggested. On FV, there's no reason that auction shouldn't be limited to city zones.  The last thing I want when tending to the young adventurers in Unrest is for someone to set up camp at the zone line and /auction WTS Ghoul heart for ghoulbane quest!<br>
<br>
It would be simple to just make /auction work only in the same zones where soul binding works...<br>
